DATA RESEARCH ADDS EBSCO DATABASES TO INFORMATION GATEWAY
 
Data Research Associates, Inc. has signed an agreement with EBSCO
Publishing to provide EBSCO's Magazine Article Summaries and
Academic Abstracts through the Data Research Information Gateway.
The EBSCO indexes are tape loaded into the library's DRA system,
where they are searched using familiar OPAC commands.
 
Magazine Article Summaries covers articles appearing in the New
York Times and 371 general interest periodicals selected for use
by school and public libraries based on EBSCO Subscription
Services' statistics.
 
Academic Abstracts covers articles appearing in the New York
Times and 757 periodicals most commonly found in academic
libraries according to EBSCO Subscription Services' statistics.
 
For further information, contact Joe Bonwich, Data Research
Associates, Inc., 1276 North Warson Road, P.O. Box 8495, St.
Louis, MO 63132-1806, (800) 325-0888.
 
 
NEW RELEASE OF SCIENCE CITATION INDEX CD-ROM PLANNED
 
The Institute for Scientific Information has announced that it
will release a new version of its Science Citation Index Compact
Disc Edition (SCI CDE).  The new edition will add English-
language author abstracts, which are available for 83% of the
indexed articles, to the database.   The new release is scheduled
for July 1992.
 
